<li id="cite_note-Linguistic_Analysis-25"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-Linguistic_Analysis_25-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Linguistic_Analysis_25-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Linguistic_Analysis_25-2"><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Linguistic_Analysis_25-3"><sup><i><b>d</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text"><span class="citation Journal">Eades, Diana (2005). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://songchau.googlepages.com/503.pdf">"Applied Linguistics and Language Analysis in Asylum Seeker Cases"</a>. <i>Applied Linguistics</i> <b>26</b> (4): 503–526. <a href="Digital_object_identifier" title="Digital object identifier">doi</a>:<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://dx.doi.org/10.1093/applin/ami021">10.1093/applin/ami021</a><span class="printonly">. <a rel="nofollow" class="external free" href="http://songchau.googlepages.com/503.pdf">http://songchau.googlepages.com/503.pdf</a></span>.</span></span></li>
